The persecution of university students for their beliefs is not new.
For as long as I can remember, I've wanted to go to Oxford.
My father and older brother attended Oxford, and described it as the best educational institution in the world, a modern analogue of the ancient symposium, laying the two foundations of civilization - free thought and tolerance.
