At other universities, conservative students complain that they are "put to death for raising tuition".
Luke Black, 20, vice-president of the Nottingham University Conservative Association, said in an interview with a Sunday newspaper that "the left-wing bias is increasing in the university environment.
People who do not even know us assume that we are the brazen, unpunished children of rich parents".
Samuel Roberts, 21, a history student at Corpus Christi College who filed for the protection, calls the atmosphere "unwelcoming", and Stephanie Cherill, 19, the new president of the Oxford University Conservative Association, says that the attitude of the student club members towards centre-rightists has deteriorated significantly.
