"He never goes out of style because his sketches are works of art", she concludes.
The parade of the lineage
Garavani's life is not a story of obsessions, but of love with complete reciprocity.
He likes people with good education and high titles, and they like him.
One of the galleries of Somerset House has been transformed into a glamorous podium sixty meters long, which offers a change of role: the visitor takes the place of the models and must walk down the podium, gazing at the "spectators" of dreadlocks that sparkle with masterpieces from Valentino, such as the dress that Jacqueline Kennedy chose for her wedding to Aristotle Onassis, the suit that Monica Vitti used in "Notti", or the coat of wool and leather that belonged to the Empress Diarra.
In this audience, such names shine through as Sibyl of Luxembourg, Gloria von Turn und Taksis, Mette-Marit of Norway, Rosario of Bulgaria or Sofia of Gabsburg.
Nati Abascal and the fashion designer, in 2006
