A keen basketball traveler, Hector "Hetin" Reyes has been associated with the sport for more than 60 years and has traveled the world thanks to it.
Few people in Puerto Rico have as much basketball history in their memory as Hector "Hatin" Reyes.
And before a brain hemorrhage left him in a wheelchair in 2008, Reyes was immersed in sports for more than 60 years, as a minor league player, a Major League Baseball player, a commissioner and executive of the BSN with the Bayamon Cowboys and president of the Basketball Federation.
